<section id="what">
 <title>What can you do?</title>
 
 <p>For <em style="strong">a single toolkit for all the widgets in your application</em>, use <em style="strong"><link xref="tech-gtk">GTK+</link></em>.</p>

 <p>To <em style="strong">create fast, visually rich graphical interfaces</em>, use <em style="strong"><link xref="tech-clutter">Clutter</link></em>.</p>

 <p>To <em style="strong">have high quality, antialiased and resolution-independent 2D graphics</em>, use <em style="strong"><link xref="tech-cairo">Cairo</link></em>.</p>

 <p>To <em style="strong">easily add web functionality to your application</em>, use <em style="strong"><link xref="tech-webkit">WebKitGTK+</link></em>.</p>

 <p>To <em style="strong">access built-in assistive technologies</em>, use <em style="strong"><link xref="tech-atk">ATK</link></em>. Orca, Caribou OSK, GTK+ built-in accessibility tools.</p>

